      "content": "i get that there are two sides, but you're being kinda vague. like, the originalist crowd says they're just looking at the text of the amendment, which seems pretty straightforward and grounded in law. then you have the other side that's basically saying the amendment should change as society changes. doesnt that make the originalist view more \"legally sound\" since it's actually tied to the document itself?",
